  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Twin Rooms</strong> are around 18m² and sleep two people. They have a bath or shower. Rooms with a balcony or terrace may be available on request.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Twin Rooms </strong>are around 22m² and sleep up to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). They have a shower and a balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites </strong>are around 30m² and sleep up to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed). They have a shower and a balcony with mountain views. These rooms are available on request, please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Standard Twins for sole use </strong>are available on request for a supplement, please call to book.</p>
<p>Please note, adjacent superior rooms are available on request, ideal for families or small groups.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Mini Fridge</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tax of approx. €2.50 per person per night is payable locally</p>
<p><strong>General Information</strong></p>
<p>Cots are available for free for children up to 2 years old (bookable locally)</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
